
Java 9 (2017) introduced modularity and several productivity improvements. The most important feature is the Module System (Project Jigsaw).

1. Module System (Project Jigsaw) 
..............................................

It allows splitting applications into modules with explicit dependencies.

Example
module-info.java
module com.bank.app {
    requires java.sql;
    exports com.bank.service;
}
Service Class
package com.bank.service;

public class AccountService {

    public void createAccount() {
        System.out.println("Account Created");
    }
}
Usage from Another Module
module com.bank.loan {
    requires com.bank.app;
}
..............................................................
Benefits
Strong encapsulation
Better security
Faster startup
Clear dependency management
2. JShell (Interactive REPL)
............................................
Java 9 introduced JShell for testing code quickly.
......................
jshell
...............................
Example
jshell> int a = 10;
jshell> int b = 20;
jshell> a + b
30
3. Factory Methods for Collections
.......................................

Immutable collections can be created easily.

List<String> list =
        List.of("A", "B", "C");

Set<Integer> set =
        Set.of(1, 2, 3);
Benefits
Immutable by default
Less boilerplate
Thread-safe
4. Stream API Improvements
................................
takeWhile()
List<Integer> list =
        List.of(1,2,3,4,5,6);

list.stream()
    .takeWhile(n -> n < 4)
    .forEach(System.out::println);

Output:

1
2
3
dropWhile()
...............................
list.stream()
    .dropWhile(n -> n < 4)
    .forEach(System.out::println);

Output:

4
5
6
5. Optional Enhancements
..........................................
ifPresentOrElse
Optional<String> name =
        Optional.of("Sunil");

name.ifPresentOrElse(
    System.out::println,
    () -> System.out.println("Empty")
);
6. Private Methods in Interfaces
..............................................................
Used to reduce code duplication in interfaces.

interface Payment {

    default void pay() {
        log();
    }

    private void log() {
        System.out.println("Logging Payment");
    }
}
7. Stream Improvements – ofNullable
............................................
Stream.ofNullable(null)
      .forEach(System.out::println);

No NullPointerException.

8. Improved Try-With-Resources
........................................
Before Java 9:

BufferedReader br =
        new BufferedReader(new FileReader("file.txt"));

try (BufferedReader reader = br) {
}

Java 9:
..............................................
BufferedReader br =
        new BufferedReader(new FileReader("file.txt"));

try (br) {
}
